                <th class="p-4 border border-gray-200 font-bold">Per Visit</th>
                <th class="p-4 border border-gray-200 font-bold">Monthly (3x/week)</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">Small Practice (under 1,500 sq ft)</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$175 - $275</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$600 - $900</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">Medium Practice (1,500-3,000 sq ft)</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$250 - $375</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$850 - $1,200</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">Large Practice (3,000-5,000 sq ft)</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$350 - $500</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$1,200 - $1,800</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">Multi-Physician Clinic (5,000+ sq ft)</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$450 - $700+</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$1,500 - $2,500+</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">Urgent Care Center</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$300 - $500</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$1,200 - $2,000</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">Dental Office (per operatory)</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$175 - $350</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$600 - $1,200</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[#FFA985]/10 p-6 rounded-xl mb-8">
          <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Pricing Factors</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
            <li>• <strong>Number of exam rooms:</strong> More rooms = more detailed work</li>
            <li>• <strong>Procedure areas:</strong> Surgical suites, treatment rooms need extra attention</li>
            <li>• <strong>Cleaning frequency:</strong> Daily vs 3x weekly affects per-visit pricing</li>
            <li>• <strong>Specialty requirements:</strong> Dermatology, oral surgery have unique needs</li>
            <li>• <strong>Location:</strong> UAB area, Mountain Brook command premium pricing</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- WHAT TO LOOK FOR -->
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">What to Look for in Medical Office Cleaning</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Not all cleaning companies can properly serve healthcare facilities. Here's what distinguishes qualified medical office cleaners:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">1. Healthcare-Specific Training</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">Ask about:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600">
              <li>✓ OSHA bloodborne pathogen training</li>
              <li>✓ HIPAA awareness training</li>
              <li>✓ Infection control protocols</li>
              <li>✓ Proper PPE usage</li>
              <li>✓ Chemical safety certification</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">2. Proper Disinfectants</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">Medical offices require:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600">
              <li>✓ EPA-registered hospital-grade disinfectants</li>
              <li>✓ Products effective against MRSA, C. diff, norovirus</li>
              <li>✓ Understanding of contact time requirements</li>
              <li>✓ Knowledge of surface compatibility</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">3. Consistent Staffing</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">Why it matters:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600">
              <li>✓ Same team learns your protocols</li>
              <li>✓ Familiar faces in sensitive environments</li>
              <li>✓ Consistency in cleaning quality</li>
              <li>✓ Accountability for your practice</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">4. Proper Insurance</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">Minimum requirements:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600">
              <li>✓ $1-2 million general liability coverage</li>
              <li>✓ Workers' compensation insurance</li>
              <li>✓ Bonding for employee dishonesty</li>
              <li>✓ Certificate naming your practice as additional insured</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- BIRMINGHAM AREAS -->
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Medical Office Cleaning by Birmingham Area</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Birmingham's medical practices are concentrated in several key areas:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-[#FFA985]/10 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">UAB Medical District / Downtown</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Alabama's largest medical center creates high demand for healthcare cleaning. Specialty clinics, research facilities, and private practices cluster around UAB. Building coordination and after-hours access are standard. Expect premium pricing ($0.18-$0.25/sq ft).</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Vestavia Hills / Highway 280</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Suburban medical offices serving the Over the Mountain communities. Dermatology, plastic surgery, and specialty practices are common. Professional presentation expectations are high. Pricing ranges $0.15-$0.22/sq ft.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Homewood / Mountain Brook</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Dental practices, pediatricians, and family medicine offices serve these affluent communities. Patients expect pristine facilities. Premium service expectations with pricing $0.16-$0.24/sq ft.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Hoover / Riverchase</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Growing medical corridor with urgent care, specialty clinics, and multi-physician practices. More moderate pricing ($0.14-$0.20/sq ft) with strong demand for quality service.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SPECIALTY PRACTICES -->
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Cleaning by Practice Specialty</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Dental Offices</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Operatory cleaning, sterilization area maintenance, and proper handling around dental equipment. Understanding of ADA infection control guidelines. See our <a href="/locations/birmingham/dental-office-cleaning" class="text-[#FFA985] font-semibold hover:underline">Birmingham dental office cleaning</a> services.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Dermatology / Plastic Surgery</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Procedure room cleaning, post-treatment area sanitation, and premium presentation for aesthetic practices. High patient expectations for cleanliness.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Urgent Care Centers</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">High-volume facilities need daily (often twice-daily) cleaning. Fast turnaround, quick-dry products, and flexible scheduling for extended hours.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Physical Therapy / Chiropractic</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Equipment sanitization, treatment table disinfection, and gym area maintenance. Shared equipment requires attention between patients.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">How much does medical office cleaning cost in Birmingham?</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              Medical office cleaning in Birmingham typically costs $175-$400+ per visit, or $0.15-$0.25 per square foot. A 2,000 sq ft practice cleaned 3x weekly runs $600-$1,200/month. Pricing depends on exam room count, procedure areas, specialty, and location.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Do medical office cleaners need HIPAA training?</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              While cleaning companies aren't "covered entities" under HIPAA, responsible medical office cleaners should have HIPAA awareness training. This includes understanding patient privacy, proper document handling, and confidentiality requirements. Quality services operate with HIPAA awareness to protect your practice.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">How often should a medical office be cleaned?</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              Most Birmingham medical practices need professional cleaning 3-5 times per week. High-volume practices and urgent care centers often need daily service. The CDC recommends daily cleaning and disinfection of high-touch surfaces in healthcare settings. Low-volume specialty practices may manage with 2-3 times weekly.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">What disinfectants should be used in medical offices?</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              Medical offices require EPA-registered hospital-grade disinfectants effective against healthcare-associated pathogens including MRSA, C. diff, norovirus, and influenza. Look for EPA List N disinfectants which meet efficacy standards. Proper contact time is critical—the disinfectant must remain wet for its specified dwell time to be effective.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Should we use the same cleaning team each visit?</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              Yes, consistent staffing is especially important for medical facilities. The same team learns your protocols, layout, and specific requirements. Staff familiarity also matters for security—you want to know who's in your practice around patient information and medical equipment. Avoid services that rotate random workers.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- CTA -->
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Get a Medical Office Cleaning Quote</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Every medical practice has unique requirements. Whether you're a solo practitioner in Homewood or a multi-physician clinic near UAB, we customize our service to your specific needs, schedule, and compliance requirements.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-8 rounded-xl text-center">
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Healthcare-Grade Cleaning for Birmingham Practices</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-6">HIPAA-aware, OSHA-trained, $2M insured.</p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
